RWE Plans $4.3 Billion Wind, Hydro Investment in Turkey, Hurriyet Reports

-- B y   S t e v e   B r y a n t
-- 
2011-04-14T05:00:34Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-14/rwe-plans-3-billion-euro-investment-in-turkey-hurriyet-reports.html
RWE AG,  Germany ’s second largest
utility, plans to invest 3 billion euros ($4.3 billion) in
 Turkey , Hurriyet newspaper reported, citing Chief Executive
Jurgen Grossman.  The timetable for the spending isn’t clear and depends on
the pace of development for projects in hydroelectric and wind
power, Grossman said in Denizli, western Turkey, where the
company broke ground for a 500-million-euro gas power plant, the
newspaper said.   Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
